## 5.3.1.4 Reports of Bioanalytical and Analytical Methods for Human Studies

Simultaneous analysis of losartan, its active metabolite, and hydrochlorothiazide in human plasma by a {{ drug.molecular_formula }}-MS/MS method.

Priyanka A. {{ drug.molecular_formula }}, Primal {{ drug.molecular_formula }}, Jaivik V. {{ drug.molecular_formula }},Mallika {{ drug.molecular_formula }}, Pranav S. {{ drug.molecular_formula }};1Department of Chemistry, School of Sciences, Gujarat University, Navrangpura, Ahmedabad, India2Department of Chemistry, St. Xavier's College, Navrangpura, Ahmedabad, India

Received:01.02.2015Accepted/Published Online:15.05.2015Printed:28.08.2015

Abstract:

A selective and sensitive ultra-performance liquid chromatography-tandem mass spectrometry method was developed for the simultaneous determination of losartan ({{ drug.molecular_formula }}), {{ drug.molecular_formula }}-3174, which is an active metabolite {{ drug.molecular_formula }} carboxylic acid, and hydrochlorothiazide ({{ drug.molecular_formula }}) in human plasma. Solid-phase extraction was carried out on OasisHLB cartridges with 100L of plasma to give an extraction recovery in the range of 88.5%{102.5% for the three analytes.Chromatography on a {{ drug.molecular_formula }} C18 column afforded baseline separation of all the analytes within 2.4 min using 1.0% formic acid in water and acetonitrile (15:85, v/v) as the mobile phase. Quantitation was performed with multiple reaction monitoring in the negative ionization mode. The response of the method was linear over a dynamic range of 0.5{500,1.0{750, and 0.25{150 ng/mL for {{ drug.molecular_formula }}, {{ drug.molecular_formula }}-3174, and {{ drug.molecular_formula }}, respectively. Extent of signal suppression/enhancement was examined through post column infusion. The effect of matrix components was evaluated by post extraction spiking and calculation of the slope of calibration lines. The method was successfully applied to a bioequivalence study of {{ drug.strength }} losartan and 12.{{ drug.strength }} hydrochlorothiazide {{ drug.dosage_form }} formulation in 65 healthy human subjects. Reproducibility of the method was shown by reanalysis of 213 incurred samples. Key words: Losartan, {{ drug.molecular_formula }}-3174, hydrochlorothiazide, solid phase extraction, {{ drug.molecular_formula }}-MS/MS, human plasma1.
